WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-DE

00:00:00.066 --> 00:00:02.950
Rune shapes, inscriptions.

00:00:02.950 --> 00:00:05.800
This is my life's work.

00:00:05.800 --> 00:00:08.350
The more I studied,
the more I began to recognize

00:00:08.350 --> 00:00:11.350
similar shapes in the stars in the sky
.

00:00:11.800 --> 00:00:15.350
And so I dedicated myself to the
work of a

00:00:15.916 --> 00:00:17.233
rune seeker.

00:00:18.550 --> 00:00:23.150
As Farrow explains, runes are
powerful and ancient inscriptions

00:00:23.150 --> 00:00:26.350
that can be set into objects
to give them more power.

00:00:26.900 --> 00:00:30.300
During the league, you can choose from


00:00:30.300 --> 00:00:33.983
a range of runes to craft items by carving symbols into relics,
thereby improving your items.

00:00:34.633 --> 00:00:38.183
When you discover a relic,
it can

00:00:38.733 --> 00:00:39.866
have between two and seven slots.

00:00:39.866 --> 00:00:42.783
The more slots,
the more powerful the encounter,

00:00:42.783 --> 00:00:45.450
but also the more options
you can choose from.

00:00:45.450 --> 00:00:47.333
At the beginning of the game,
you can craft runes for

00:00:47.333 --> 00:00:49.400
additional damage or
resistances,

00:00:49.750 --> 00:00:51.116
which are available at a lower level

00:00:51.116 --> 00:00:52.616
than you would normally
obtain,

00:00:52.700 --> 00:00:54.433
which can be very useful.

00:00:54.650 --> 00:00:56.516
But there are far more interesting
results.

00:00:57.250 --> 00:01:00.233
There are 22 runes that
add or modify Rune Protection,

00:01:00.483 --> 00:01:02.450
a new resource that
can protect you from death.

00:01:03.033 --> 00:01:06.900
With these runes you can
add extra defense or transform your runic protection

00:01:06.900 --> 00:01:10.150
 
into an offensive weapon through Kalguuric skills.

00:01:13.183 --> 00:01:16.600
There are also 13 runes that
grant power to certain weapon types, such as

00:01:16.800 --> 00:01:19.833
this one, which gives grenades a chance
to explode a second time.

00:01:21.283 --> 00:01:24.566
Or this one, which grants you a new buff
called "Druid's Power"

00:01:24.616 --> 00:01:26.200
when you severely stun your opponents.

00:01:28.950 --> 00:01:29.850
In addition, there are

00:01:29.850 --> 00:01:32.850
22 runes designed to
give you more power at lower levels,

00:01:32.850 --> 00:01:35.850
such as this one, which grants you some
elemental resistances,

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:38.683
or this one, which
grants you a lot of willpower.

00:01:38.683 --> 00:01:42.300
These runes are said to be powerful,
but their value decreases with increasing level.

00:01:42.300 --> 00:01:45.300
They are useful for
quickly leveling up a second character.

00:01:45.733 --> 00:01:47.933
We also have six runes
that can be used

00:01:47.933 --> 00:01:51.016
to expand the pool of modifiers when crafting
at higher levels.

00:01:51.600 --> 00:01:55.133
For example, you can encase "Katla's Darkness"
in gloves,

00:01:55.133 --> 00:01:58.516
thus enabling the creation of some new
modifiers for "Decay"

00:01:58.600 --> 00:02:00.650
that can be used for "Damage over Time" builds
.

00:02:01.216 --> 00:02:03.316
Once you have framed one of these rune types
,

00:02:03.316 --> 00:02:06.416
you can craft these modifiers using regular
Exalted Spheres or Chaos Spheres.

00:02:08.666 --> 00:02:10.583
There are also several runes that

00:02:10.583 --> 00:02:13.900
apply powerful, one-time effects to items,
but are permanently bound to the socket,

00:02:14.066 --> 00:02:17.183
like this one, which allows an item to
receive an additional suffix.

00:02:21.200 --> 00:02:23.516
Or this one, with which you can create a jewel setting
.

00:02:29.166 --> 00:02:30.400
Or this series of runes

00:02:30.400 --> 00:02:33.566
that can convert an elemental modifier from one
element to another.

00:02:34.933 --> 00:02:37.700
There is even a rune that
can upgrade any other rune, allowing

00:02:37.700 --> 00:02:39.750
you to upgrade it beyond the normal
maximum.

00:02:42.133 --> 00:02:45.133
The last one I want to show you today
is "Aldur's Legacy".

00:02:45.433 --> 00:02:50.266
A special rune that can be encased in a unique Kalguurian or
Ezomyte item to destroy it,

00:02:50.266 --> 00:02:53.233
thereby creating a new rune that
inherits some of the unique item's properties.

00:02:53.816 --> 00:02:54.983
For example, you can

00:02:54.983 --> 00:02:58.350
apply this to "Trampelzeh" to
create a "Legacy: Trampelzeh" rune.

00:02:58.500 --> 00:02:59.950
Put these into any boots and,

00:02:59.950 --> 00:03:01.683
as with the original unique item,

00:03:01.683 --> 00:03:05.233
you will deal 10% of the excess damage to all
enemies within a two-meter radius.

00:03:05.983 --> 00:03:08.700
Or how about
"Legacy: Distorted Light Sky"?

00:03:08.700 --> 00:03:10.466
Destroy a "Distorted Light Sky"

00:03:10.466 --> 00:03:13.666
and you can add cold damage to a weapon
based on your maximum mana.

00:03:14.783 --> 00:03:17.900
With "Aldur's Legacy" you can create
over 100 additional runes

00:03:17.900 --> 00:03:19.950
with all sorts of unique
effects.

00:03:22.516 --> 00:03:25.116
At this point you might be thinking:
"That's a lot of new runes."

00:03:25.116 --> 00:03:26.350
And you are right.

00:03:26.350 --> 00:03:28.350
The league isn't called
"Runes of Aldur" for nothing.

00:03:28.350 --> 00:03:31.000
But we haven't forgotten the ancient runes either
.  We have improved

00:03:31.000 --> 00:03:32.700
a significant number of these old runes

00:03:32.700 --> 00:03:34.800
that were not in use,


00:03:34.800 --> 00:03:37.233
 
making this crafting system much more useful.

00:03:37.566 --> 00:03:39.183
Discover everything the new runes have to offer in the "Return of the Ancients" update,

00:03:39.183 --> 00:03:42.883
which will be released on May 29th.  See you then
!

